{"title": "Truenorth ecosystem for brain-inspired computing: scalable systems, software, and applications.", "fields": ["science technology and society", "firmware", "scalability", "truenorth", "software ecosystem", "cuda", "search engine", "software"], "abstract": "This paper describes the hardware and software ecosystem encompassing the brain-inspired TrueNorth processor - a 70mW reconfigurable silicon chip with 1 million neurons, 256 million synapses, and 4096 parallel and distributed neural cores. For systems, we present a  scale-out  system loosely coupling 16 single-chip boards and a  scale-up  system tightly integrating 16 chips in a 4 \u00d7 4 configuration by exploiting TrueNorth's native tiling. For software, we present an end-to-end ecosystem consisting of a simulator, a programming language, an integrated programming environment, a library of algorithms and applications, firmware, tools for deep learning, a teaching curriculum, and cloud enablement. For the scale-up systems we summarize our approach to physical placement of neural network, to reduce intra- and inter-chip network traffic. The ecosystem is in use at over 30 universities and government/corporate labs. Our platform is a substrate for a spectrum of applications from mobile and embedded computing to cloud and supercomputers.", "citation": "Not cited", "departments": ["IBM", "IBM", "IBM", "IBM", "IBM"], "authors": ["Jun Sawada.....http://dblp.org/pers/hd/s/Sawada:Jun", "Filipp Akopyan.....http://dblp.org/pers/hd/a/Akopyan:Filipp", "Andrew S. Cassidy.....http://dblp.org/pers/hd/c/Cassidy:Andrew_S=", "Brian Taba.....http://dblp.org/pers/hd/t/Taba:Brian", "Michael V. DeBole.....http://dblp.org/pers/hd/d/DeBole:Michael_V=", "Pallab Datta.....http://dblp.org/pers/hd/d/Datta:Pallab", "Rodrigo Alvarez-Icaza.....http://dblp.org/pers/hd/a/Alvarez=Icaza:Rodrigo", "Arnon Amir.....http://dblp.org/pers/hd/a/Amir:Arnon", "John V. Arthur.....http://dblp.org/pers/hd/a/Arthur:John_V=", "Alexander Andreopoulos..